snippet.textDisplay:
People saying "he didn't follow the rules" are missing something.

He followed the rules and all the protocols to play in AO.
Exemptions are part of both AO and visa processes and were given by independent doctors panels.
5 other unvaccinated tennis players, unvaccinated rugby players from Europe... came in without issue.

Novak's team made one mistake in the immigration form (not proven to be a "lie") among dozens of protocols but this was ruled by a court in his favour. 

The motive for the minister invoking section 133a procedure is not about this.
Wether or not it's justified to invoke such procedure intended to be used in case of extreme threats is another question.
